# Tailwind CSS Guidelines

## Configuration
- Maintain single tailwind.config.js or .ts at project root
- Define custom colors in theme.extend.colors
- Define custom spacing in theme.extend.spacing
- Document custom utility classes

## Usage Patterns
- Use utility classes directly in JSX
- Extract common patterns to @apply in CSS files
- Create custom components for frequently used patterns
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use dark: variant for dark mode support

## Tailwind Plus Components
- Reference the component library in documentation
- Maintain consistent styling across Tailwind Plus adaptations
- Extend components rather than override when possible
- Document any customizations to Tailwind Plus components

## Best Practices
- Group related utilities (layout, typography, colors)
- Use arbitrary values sparingly
- Extract complex combinations to component props
- Add comments for non-obvious utility combinations
- Use clsx/classnames for conditional classes